","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/btaille/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-04-25T16:01:29Z","updated_at":"2019-04-25T16:01:29Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Thanks for your answer.\r\n\r\nIn this case I think you cannot compare directly your RE results to (Li and Ji 2014), (Miwa and Bansal 2016) and (Katiyar and Cardie 2017).\r\n\r\n(Bekoulis 2018) defines 3 evaluation types : \r\n\r\n> 1.  _Strict_: an entity is considered correct if the boundaries and the type of the entity are both correct; a relation is correct when the type of the relation and the argument entities are both correct,\r\n> 2. _Boundaries_: an entity is considered correct if only the boundaries of the entity are correct (entity type is not considered); a relation is correct when the type of the relation and the argument entities are both correct and\r\n> 3. _Relaxed_: we score a multi-token entity as correct if at least one of its comprising token types is correct assuming that the boundaries are given; a relation is correct when the type of the relation and the argument entities are both correct.\r\n\r\nAs far as I understand (Miwa and Bansal 2016) and (Katiyar and Cardie 2017) use _Strict_ evaluation and  (Li and Ji 2014) uses _Boundaries_. Your evaluation would lie in between _Boundaries_ and _Relaxed_.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/huggingface/hmtl/issues/comments/486734689/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"